title.narrative: Health for Life (Core Contract)

description.narrative: (Nepal): Health for Life (H4L) aims to strengthen the Ministry of Health's (MOH) capacity to plan, manage and deliver quality and equitable services in family planning (service delivery and policy strengthening), maternal (birth preparedness and obstetric complications), newborn (care and treatment), and child health (improving treatment of child illness)...With FY 2017 funds, H4L will continue its core interventions in14 focus districts, including the continued rollout of a service delivery quality improvement system at the district level, revitalizing health facility management committees, ensuring the use of local data for decision making, and supporting the MOH to address the gap between research findings, programming, and policy...USAID will continue to provide support in 10 of the 14 most earthquake-affected districts, to reestablish information systems, ensure the use of data for local health planning, and to coordinate health facility reconstruction.
